        <scopecontent>
          <p>The largest series in the collection is the Correspondence which dates from 1908 to 1949 with most of the files falling in the period of the 1920s when Comstock was active in business and in the affairs of the state Democratic Party. Correspondence for the period when he was governor and after are slight. The series, although labeled as Correspondence, also includes a mixture of other types of business and legal documentation. The correspondence is of most importance for its documentation of Comstock as a successful man of business.</p>
        </scopecontent>
